Pantheon Living Ecology

Canonical Architecture v1.0

“Knowledge survives not because it is stored, but because it lives.”

⸻

Purpose

Pantheon is not a library.

It is not a database.

It is not merely a graph.

Pantheon is a living semantic ecosystem.

Every artifact is a living participant whose survival depends upon its ability to contribute to the health of the whole.

Growth is ecological rather than accumulative.

